ZH: 不要贬低自己的能力。
EN: Don't underestimate your own abilities.

ZH: 他总是贬低别人的努力。
EN: He always puts down others' efforts.

ZH: 她的批评总是贬低我们的价值。
EN: Her criticism always devalues our worth.

ZH: 你的言语不应该贬低他人。
EN: Your words should not belittle others.

ZH: 社会上有人喜欢贬低他人来显得自己优秀。
EN: Some people in society like to depreciate others to make themselves look better.

ZH: 不要贬低别人的努力，因为每个人都有不同的价值。
EN: Do not diminish others' efforts, as everyone has different value.

ZH: 这种贬低的言语会伤害他人的感情。
EN: Such depreciating words can hurt others' feelings.

ZH: 不要用贬低的语言来评价他人的外貌。
EN: Do not use derogatory language to judge others' appearance.

ZH: 贬低别人只能显示自己的无能。
EN: Belittling others only shows one's incompetence.

ZH: 不要用贬低的态度对待欠缺自信的人。
EN: Do not treat people lacking confidence with a belittling attitude.

ZH: 她经常自我贬低，缺乏自信。
EN: She often self-depreciates and lacks confidence.

ZH: 贬低别人不会让自己变得更好。
EN: Disparaging others will not make oneself better.

ZH: 不要贬低自己的成就，应该为自己感到骄傲。
EN: Do not devalue your own achievements, you should be proud of yourself.

ZH: 骄傲的人往往喜欢贬低别人。
EN: Proud people often like to belittle others.

ZH: 别人的成功不应该被贬低。
EN: Others' success should not be diminished.

ZH: 她总是用贬低的态度对待失败者。
EN: She always treats failures with a belittling attitude.

ZH: 不要贬低他人的梦想，尊重他们的选择。
EN: Do not diminish others' dreams, respect their choices.

ZH: 贬低他人并不能证明自己的优越。
EN: Diminishing others does not prove one's superiority.

ZH: 贬低别人只会让自己显得更加卑劣。
EN: Belittling others only makes oneself appear more despicable.
